      "created_at": "2023-12-15T17:49:46.362Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Couple questions on the details of this feature:</p>\n<p>Seems like regardless of the mode I choose in the app, I have to specify slope in the interval type to get the slope to automatically change.  Does this mean that if I switch to erg mode in the app, it will switch back to slope at the start of the next interval (if both intervals are marked as a slope interval type)?  What if I have work intervals marked as slope and rest as rest (no mode specified)?  If I switch to erg in the app, do the work intervals change?  What about the subsequent rest intervals?</p>\n<p>In other words, how do the interval type and app mode interact?</p>",
